      <hedline>
        <hl1>Unfit for the West Village</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Angela Dominguez letter comments on May 25 article on the architect Richard Meier</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Richard Meier's attitude, in your article ''Richard Meier Builds in Manhattan. At Last.'' (May 25), is typical of those developers who descend on quiet neighborhoods like the West Village.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Richard Meier's attitude, in your article ''Richard Meier Builds in Manhattan. At Last.'' (May 25), is typical of those developers who descend on quiet neighborhoods like the West Village.</p>
        <p>The building in which I live will be directly affected by ''Meiercity.'' The views Mr. Meier brags about in your article are the same views he'll be taking from us. The shadows alone caused by these two towers will make our airy, light neighborhood feel like Midtown.</p>
        <p>ANGELA DOMINGUEZ  New York</p>
      </block>
